        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 27 at 7:07PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 707 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Jack Brown Estates, or
8 miles north of Fort Valley, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Jack Brown Estates.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
